   "source": [
    "# Section 8 — SHAP Analysis & Molecular Toxicity Highlighting\n",
    "\n",
    "**Add this notebook's cells after Section 7 in your main solution notebook.**\n",
    "\n",
    "This section answers: *what is the model actually learning?*\n",
    "\n",
    "We use SHAP (SHapley Additive exPlanations) to:\n",
    "1. Identify which Morgan fingerprint bits most influence LD50 predictions\n",
    "2. Map those bits back to specific atoms in a molecule\n",
    "3. Draw molecules with atoms colored by their toxicity contribution\n",
    "4. Find recurring 'toxic substructures' across the dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "This turns our black-box model into something a medicinal chemist can actually use."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "sec8-0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
