   "id": "sec8-1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8.1 Compute SHAP Values\n",
    "\n",
    "We use `shap.TreeExplainer` — it's fast and exact for tree-based models like XGBoost.  \n",
    "It computes a SHAP value for every feature for every molecule.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Positive SHAP value** → this feature pushes the prediction UP (higher log LD50 = less toxic)\n",
    "- **Negative SHAP value** → this feature pushes the prediction DOWN (lower log LD50 = more toxic)\n",
    "\n",
    "We use the validation set (a random sample of 500 molecules) to keep it fast."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "compute-shap",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import shap\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from rdkit import Chem\n",
    "from rdkit.Chem import AllChem, Draw\n",
    "from rdkit.Chem.Draw import rdMolDraw2D\n",
    "from IPython.display import display, Image\n",
    "import io\n",
    "from PIL import Image as PILImage\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Use a sample of the validation set for speed\n",
    "# (SHAP on full training set can take 10+ minutes)\n",
    "N_SAMPLE = 500\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "sample_idx = np.random.choice(len(X_valid), size=N_SAMPLE, replace=False)\n",
    "X_sample = X_valid[sample_idx]\n",
    "y_sample = y_valid[sample_idx]\n",
    "smiles_sample = valid_df['Drug'].values[sample_idx]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Computing SHAP values for {N_SAMPLE} molecules...')\n",
    "print('(This takes ~1-3 minutes for XGBoost)')\n",
    "\n",
    "# TreeExplainer is fast + exact for XGBoost/RF\n",
    "explainer = shap.TreeExplainer(xgb_model)\n",
    "shap_values = explainer.shap_values(X_sample)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'SHAP values shape: {shap_values.shape}')\n",
    "print(f'  → {shap_values.shape[0]} molecules × {shap_values.shape[1]} features')\n",
    "print(f'  → First 2048 features = Morgan fingerprint bits')\n",
    "print(f'  → Last {shap_values.shape[1]-2048} features = physicochemical descriptors')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "sec8-2",
   "metadata": {},
